Gg_stoo_elcastillo_rmx -------------------------- This is a remix of gg_elcastillo. It's been rebuilt almost from scratch. The original was really inefficient. Lots of brushes inside brushes, overlapping brushes and missing textures. I thought the idea had promise, and I like Maya architecture and culture, so I decided to remake it. El Castillo is Spanish for "The Castle". It's the nickname given to the Temple of Kukulcan in the Maya city of Chichen Itza in Mexico. Most of the textures and decals were modified or created by myself. Many of them are actual Maya symbols or patterns, but they were placed at random in the map and don't really mean anything. The teleport inside the pyramid teleports you to one of the 4 corners on top of the building at random, so camping the teleport destinations should be difficult. The original version of the map is more realistic, but this version should be faster, smoother and generally more fun. Yes, you can shoot through the star in the floor/ceiling, but you cannot break it. :) Cheers to PresumedDead who made the original gg_elcastillo! StOo (www.betaneutral.com) Thanks for playing! 03.07.2007

Gg_stoo_czktwo ----------------- * THIS IS AN IMPROVED AND EXTENDED VERSION OF GG_STOO_CHINZAK_DEVTEX I played the map a bit and got some constructive criticism. Plus I'm a perfectionist who can't just leave things alone. Added proper bot support! Bots can do _almost_ everything players can do in the map, including go to the roof, shoot out the windows, etc. There will be times when the bots do something really stupid - like fall to their deaths or simply get stuck - but this is about the best I can do with a map of this type. Small ledges, lots of ladders and even stairs are pretty hard for the bots to handle. They definitely prefer horizontal maps. On the other hand, the bots can easily "see" you through the glass when you might only just be able to see them, so they do provide some challenge, and they CAN traverse almost all of the map successfully when they feel like it. :) Adding the bot support was by far the most difficult and time-consuming part of making the map. You'll see a message about needing to run a full nav_analyse. I've run nav_analyse on it several times and this message won't go away. I think the nav may be a bit screwed but I can't be bothered doing it again. It works as well as I'm willing to make it work. :P Used highest quality RAD so compile time was considerably longer than before. BSP :: 6 seconds elapsed VIS :: 56 seconds elapsed RAD :: 34 minutes, 12 seconds elapsed Hopefully this will be the final version... A full changelog is below. Cheers again to _TIF_ who made the original dm_chinzak! StOo (www.betaneutral.com) Thanks for playing! 16.06.2007 V2 CHANGELOG ------------ ADDED: * Bot support! 100% hand-crafted .nav file! (Don't expect miracles! It's a difficult map for bots, to say the least.) * Ladders inside each tower from ground to top floor. Now you have 2 ways to get to every level. (stairs and ladders) * Expanded upper levels, more room to move! * Small stack of crates in the middle of the courtyard outside. * Hint brushes. Hopefully doing more good than harm. * Top floor on CT side to match T side. The two towers are now almost completely identical in layout! * Various cosmetic brushwork. (borders on windows etc.) REMOVED: * Removed 2 of the water pools in the courtyard. Makes it slightly harder to bail out of a window in the middle of a firefight. :) CHANGED: * Fixed MANY texture alignment errors. * Fixed MANY brush alignment errors. * Reduced the quality of the cubemaps slightly. They were a bit OTT and performance suffered. * Shorter mapname! Easier to type! ;) * Enlarged main doors and made them func_door instead of func_door_rotating, so now they slide. * Made all windows much easier to break! * Made the ladders to the roof easier to climb by rounding them slightly and removing the overhang at the top. * Made the roofs all the same height, and simplified their design. * Made all the "light fixtures" non-solid coz they were getting in the way. :P * Changed 2D skybox from train to militia. * Reduced ambient light level very slightly. * Enlarged sun very slightly. * Used -final vrad directive for highest quality lightmaps, hence the 30 min RAD time.

Gg_stoo_chinzak_devtex ---------------------------- *** IMPORTANT NOTE *** I'VE RELEASED A SECOND, IMPROVED VERSION OF THIS MAP. YOU CAN FIND IT HERE: GG_STOO_CZKTWO. I'M KEEPING THIS VERSION AROUND FOR POSTERITY, AND IN CASE ANYONE PREFERS IT TO THE NEW ONE. This took a few days to do, on and off. Almost everything in the map has been altered in some way. The other Chinzak for GG is barely altered from the original DM map. People would leave the server when it came on, saying it was too laggy or too hard to navigate. This map is a response to those complaints. Should be considerably easier to navigate than the original DM map. Should also run considerably faster despite having high-res cubemaps and high-res lightmaps. This is the first release so there may be problems I haven't found on my own. If so, I'll release a fixed version. Features a few custom textures created by me. Learning Photoshop as I go. Compile time on my very average PC was 5 mins exactly. VBSP took about 2 seconds. VVIS took about 5 seconds. VRAD took about 4 mins 53 seconds. :) Hope you enjoy playing this map as much as I enjoyed making it. Cheers to _TIF_ who made the original DM map in the first place! Gg_stalker_arena 1.1
------------------------

This is a map remake of the arena found in S.T.A.L.K.E.R: Shadow of Chernobyl. 
It's actually a small arena in game but the size of my map turned out bigger. :S
I remade it as best I could, looking at the most simple of details to remake it in it's shining image but with limited textures and props, it isn't exact. (I had to add some extra cover for the sake of balance.)

The map features:
-Buyzones 
-HDR 
-60 spawn points

Have fun stalker.

Hey folks, this is my newest, latest map. It is a large-ish map compared to some other gungame maps. it consists of 2 floors and 3 main areas which are, the outer ring, the inner room, ad the underground laser tag area. The outer ring consists of boxes and stairs used for maneuvering and for finding cover, the inner building is for quick rushes and fast firefights, and the underground laser tag area is for close quarters combat and unsuspecting knife kills from behind. It can hold up to 24 players. Thank you for checking out my map and I hope you enjoy this as well as my other maps :) Please rate and leave comments below and don't for get to download!

Some places may look safe, like the glass room, but it and the other secret rooms are actually very lethal and won't hesitate to kill you...
